Basic concepts and keywords of the field of geology are given. Students' career planning skills are developed during the course.
We advise the first-year bachelor students of geology and environmental technology curriculum to register during first autumn semester also for the introductory practical course LOOM.00.031 "Applications of Geology and Environmental Technology".Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of this course is to introduce students' history and current state of geology in Estonia and career opportunities in this field. The course gives an introduction to the field of geology, its general terms, structure, and terminology. The course develops students' career planning skills.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completion of the course student knows:  - different career opportunities in the geology field; - has a background knowledge of history and current situation in geology; - basic concepts and theoretical principles of geology; - actual problems in the geology field;  - is able to plan, decide and act based on personal learning goals, making informed choices both in the acquisition of professional electives and in the selection of the dissertation project and supervisor. - analyses and targets their professional study and studies and career choices.
